1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper discusses learning local descriptors for keypoint matching, which is a common problem in computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper describes an end-to-end differentiable architecture for learning local descriptors from weakly labeled data. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses learning features from unlabeled video signals and 3D models, which are common tasks in AI. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses learning features from video signals, which is a common task in multimedia analysis. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses 3D shape retrieval, which is a common problem in computer graphics.
